Reasoning: 

- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the culture and practices of software development that have fostered the success of the VisIt visualization system. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper discusses efforts to encourage research and support production software. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper mentions measuring impact, which could relate to digital library metrics. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper may discuss user-centered design and user experience in the development of VisIt. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as the paper discusses visualization and the development of a visualization system.
